East London police in the Eastern Cape arrested five armed robbery suspects, aged between 19 and 32, in Mdantsane NU-5, yesterday.Spokesperson Captain Nkosikho Mzuku said police had also confiscated two firearms during the intelligence-driven operation.Police pounced on the suspects early yesterday and confiscated two 9mm pistols, a pellet gun, 15 rounds of ammunition and stolen cellphones.Mzuku said two of the suspects were charged with the illegal possession of firearms, and the other three were charged with the possession of suspected stolen goods.One of the suspects is a Somalian national.Mzuku said the firearms would be sent for ballistic tests in order to establish whether they had been used in any criminal acts.The five men are expected to appear in the Mdantsane Magistrate s Court today. ANA